Select Works of Aimee Semple McPherson (3 vols.)

by McPherson, Aimee Semple 
•

N.P., Aimee Semple McPherson, The Bridal Call Publishing House 1919–1921








				Runs on Windows, Mac and mobile.
			







$20.99









 Add to cart




















Tweet










Overview
This collection of works by Charismatic revivalist, faith healer, and powerful preacher Aimee Semple McPherson contains her passionate preaching about Christ, addresses the Holy Spirit’s indwelling of believers, and discusses the importance of Jesus’ return. McPherson’s powerful preaching in 1920s Los Angeles mobilized and attracted a great number of followers. This collection illustrates what made her teaching so compelling and will gain a perspective on this influential preacher in American church history. These examples from her prodigious output will benefit those who wish to understand her mark on the subsequent Charismatic church movement and her season of influential ministry at the Angelus Temple.

In the Logos editions, these volumes are enhanced by amazing functionality. Important terms link to dictionaries, encyclopedias, and a wealth of other resources in your digital library. Perform powerful searches to find exactly what you’re looking for. Take the discussion with you using tablet and mobile apps. With Logos Bible Software, the most efficient and comprehensive research tools are in one place, so you get the most out of your study.

For more Pentecostal/Charismatic resources, check out the Charisma House Bundle.



Key Features

Offers sermons that are both ecumenical and focused on the work of the Holy Spirit
Contains evangelical messages that call for decision
Provides examples of early twentieth-century Charismatic teaching

 
Back to Top




Product Details

Title: Select Works of Aimee Semple McPherson
Author: Aimee Semple McPherson
Volumes: 3
Pages: 951
Christian Group: Pentecostal/Charismatic
Resource Type: Collected Works
Topic: Practical Life

 
Back to Top





Individual Titles


The Second Coming of Christ: Is He Coming? How is He Coming? When is He Coming? For Whom is He Coming?
Divine Healing Sermons
This Is That: Personal Experiences, Sermons and Writings of Aimee Semple McPherson, Evangelist

 
Back to Top





 

The Second Coming of Christ: Is He Coming? How is He Coming? When is He Coming? For Whom is He Coming?

Author: Aimee Semple McPherson
Publisher: Aimee Semple McPherson
Publication Date: 1921
Pages: 120

Sample Pages: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5 | 6 | 7




This scripturally supported study of the return of Jesus provides readers with clear evidence for Jesus’ imminent return. Because much of McPherson’s preaching (up to 22 sermons a week) was focused on moving her audience to a decision, her writing is also filled with many moving examples and illustrations that teach to the heart. Modern Christians will see timeless truths in a new way and will better understand the weighty implications of Jesus’ promise to return as reigning king.




 

Divine Healing Sermons

Author: Aimee Semple McPherson
Publisher: Aimee Semple McPherson
Publication Date: 1921
Pages: 146

Sample Pages: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5 | 6 | 7




This volume contains hope-filled sermons on the themes of God’s work in the modern world, the scriptural relationship between salvation and healing, frequently asked questions about divine healing, and more. These sermons are filled with powerful rhetoric and turns of phrase that assist readers and hearers to live in light of God’s Word.




 

This Is That: Personal Experiences, Sermons and Writings of Aimee Semple McPherson, Evangelist

Author: Aimee Semple McPherson
Publisher: Bridal Call Publishing House
Publication Date: 1920
Pages: 685

Sample Pages: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5 | 6 | 7




This book contains the story of Aimee Semple McPherson, from simple agrarian life to nation-wide fame as a preacher and teacher. This account includes her baptism in the Holy Spirit, evangelistic campaigns, and ministry career. Readers will benefit from her story as well as her teaching in this focused study.




 
Back to Top




About Aimee Semple McPherson
Aimee Semple McPherson (1890–1944) was a prominent evangelist in Los Angeles and founder of the International Church of the Foursquare Gospel. She performed public healings, promoted the idea of America as a nation particularly blessed by God, engaged in charity work, and became a model that many Charismatic churches emulated and followed. Her ministry casts a long shadow on this movement within the modern American church.

 
Back to Top








