Product Description▼▲
In 1915, Aimee Semple McPherson began traveling around the United States, holding tent revivals with some crowds reaching well over thirty thousand people. The tent revivals of this vivacious and spirited speaker would last weeks in any given city across the country. She used a brass band, choirs, and props of all sorts in her sermons.During her ministry, tens of thousands of people were healed when Aimee prayed for them, but she herself took no credit for the healings, instead giving full credit to God. She insisted that divine healing was not found in the emergency room, the world of entertainment, or in the scientist's laboratory; it was a church sacrament, accessible by faith and devotion alone.Divine Healing Sermons is a collection of the messages McPherson preached during her amazing ministry. They remain as powerful and accessible today as they were a century ago.

Product Information▼▲
Format: PaperbackNumber of Pages: 128Vendor: Whitaker HousePublication Date: 2014Dimensions: 9.00 X 6.00 X 0.50 (inches)ISBN: 1603749578ISBN-13: 9781603749572

